    "plan_content": "## Plan: Add `Bun.INI` Namespace\n\nHere's my complete implementation plan after studying all the relevant source files.\n\n---\n\n### Files to change (5 total, 1 new)\n\n| # | File | Change |\n|---|---|---|\n| 1 | `src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig` | **CREATE** — self-contained INI parse + stringify |\n| 2 | `src/bun.js/api/BunObject.zig` | 3 small additions to wire it in |\n| 3 | `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject+exports.h` | Add `macro(INI)` |\n| 4 | `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject.cpp` | Add hash-table entry |\n| 5 | `packages/bun-types/bun.d.ts` | Add `namespace INI` with JSDoc |\n\n---\n\n### Step 1 — `INIObject.zig` (new file)\n\nFollows **JSON5Object.zig** as primary pattern (parse + stringify). Completely self-contained — no dependency on the internal npm INI parser.\n\n- **`create`**: builds JS object with `parse` and `stringify` JSFunctions (capacity 2)\n- **`parse`**: tokenizes input by `\\n`, skips blank lines and `;`/`#` comments, matches `[section]` headers (creating nested sub-objects on the root), splits `key = value` on first `=` with whitespace trimming, throws `\"INI Parse error: invalid line: ...\"` on bad input\n- **`stringify`**: two-pass iteration — first emits top-level scalar values as `key = value`, then emits nested objects as `[section]` blocks; uses `wtf.StringBuilder`\n\n---\n\n### Step 2 — `BunObject.zig` (3 additions)\n\n- **~line 65** (before `JSONC`): `pub const INI = toJSLazyPropertyCallback(Bun.getINIObject);`\n- **~line 1287** (alongside `getYAMLObject`): `pub fn getINIObject(globalThis, _) { return INIObject.create(globalThis); }`\n- **~line 2082** (alongside other `XxxObject` imports): `const INIObject = bun.api.INIObject;`\n\n---\n\n### Step 3 — `BunObject+exports.h`\n\nAdd `macro(INI) \\` between `macro(Glob)` and `macro(JSON5)` in `FOR_EACH_GETTER` (alphabetical order: G → **I** → J).\n\n---\n\n### Step 4 — `BunObject.cpp`\n\nAdd to `@begin bunObjectTable` near the JSONC/JSON5/TOML/YAML block:\n```\nINI    BunObject_lazyPropCb_wrap_INI    DontDelete|PropertyCallback\n```\n\n---\n\n### Step 5 — `bun.d.ts`\n\nInsert `namespace INI` with `parse(input: string): Record<string, any>` and `stringify(input: Record<string, any>): string`, with JSDoc examples, after the `TOML` namespace (line 794) and before `JSONC` (line 796).",
